description: Framework for the analysis of air traffic conflict detection and resolution algorithms
Formalization of affine arithmetic and strategy for evaluating polynomial functions with variables on interval domains.
Real analysis, limits, continuity, derivatives, integrals.
Denotational semantics of Answer Set Programming.
Support definitions and properties for aviation-related formalizations.
Sequences of countable length defined as co-algebraic datatypes.
Directed graphs: circuits, maximal subtrees, paths, DAGs.
Exact real arithmetic including trig functions.
Examples of application of the functionality provided by NASALib.

Interval arithmetic and numerical approximations. Includes automated strategies numerical for computing numerical approximations and interval for checking satisfiability and validity of simply quantified real-valued formulas. This development includes a formalization of Allen interval temporal logic.
Integer division, gcd, mod, prime factorization, min, max.
Lebesgue integral with connection to Riemann Integral.
Logarithm, exponential and hyperbolic functions. & Foundational definitions of logarithm, exponential and hyperbolic functions.
Executable specification of MxN matrices. This library includes computation of inverse and basic matrix operations such as addition and multiplication.
Integration of MetiTarski, an automated theorem prover for real-valued functions.
Domains with a distance metric, continuity and uniform continuity.
Summations, sup, inf, sqrt over the reals, absolute value, etc.
Power series, comparison test, ratio test, Taylor's theorem.
Power sets, orders, cardinality over infinite sets. Includes functional and relational facts based on Axiom of Choice and refinement relations based on equivalence relations.
Bounded arrays, finite sequences, bags, and several other structures.
Formalization of Sturm's theorem for univariate polynomials. Includes strategies sturm and mono-poly for automatically proving univariate polynomial relations over a real interval.
Formalization of Tarski's theorem for univariate polynomials. Includes strategy tarski for automatically proving systems of univariate polynomial relations on the real line.
Continuity, homeomorphisms, connected and compact spaces, Borel sets/functions.
Term rewrite systems and Robinson unification algorithm.
Limits, continuity, and derivatives of vector functions.
Semantics for the programming language While.
